# User vocabulary lists and Unit 9 lexical content

- When the user supplies a new keyword list (often in Russian with glosses, or a mix), **treat the agreed English headwords and senses as the single source of truth** and **propagate the same items across** Word Bank, lexical games (drop, MCQ, express, match, **definition flip cards**, sticky board, prep vault, Tic-Tac-Toe, trainers, and any other Level-9 or topic-bound surfaces that draw from the same data files or `ART_REST_LISTEN_DATA`-style objects.

- **Definition cards (flip) — no spoilers on the front**
  - The **front** must be **plain English sense only** (or a paraphrase that does not quote the target collocation, idiom, or the exact line from the script).
  - The **back** is where the learner sees: **(1) the target phrase / headword** and **(2) the in-context line from the text** (where the pack is listening-based), not both mixed into the “definition” side.
  - Do not repeat the key phrase, its obvious morphological form, or the `ans` transcript chunk inside the front `definition` text. If a gloss would “give the game away,” rephrase the definition until it is safe.

- If the user asks to **remove a phrase** from a pack, remove it from the **shared data object** (e.g. `js/art-restoration-listen-data.js`) and anywhere else that duplicates that row, not only one screen.
